{"id":14881299,"mediaExerciseId":"2b03ae02-459c-4307-8021-51255509906d","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"11","chapterTitle":"Project Analysis and Evaluation","groupId":612352,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":376,"solutions":[{"id":6081032,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"Given that the primary concern of the company is the profitability of project, it means that they are not too concerned with adjusting the costs as long as they get profit. This means that to address this issue, we can simply manipulate the values of the sale price. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"For the computation of this, we can keep the same values for all other variables and simply use the best-case price for the sale price.\n\nThis will give us the following values:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Quantity}&=85,000\\\\\n\\text{Fixed cost}&=\\$3,900,000\\\\\n\\text{Variable cost}&=\\$460\\\\\n\\text{Sale price}&=\\$1440 \\times 1.15\\\\\n&=\\$1656\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"We will use these values since the sale price has the largest impact to the profitability of the product when all other variables are held constant. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"a4b67d34-016b-4c99-852a-b374e57794f3","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71b